       fhir:definition [ fhir:v "A set of security labels that define which resources are controlled by this exception. If more than one label is specified, all resources must have all the specified labels." ] ;
       fhir:comment [ fhir:v "If the consent specifies a security label of \"R\" then it applies to all resources that are labeled \"R\" or lower. E.g. for Confidentiality, it's a high water mark. For other kinds of security labels, subsumption logic applies. Not all of the security labels make sense for use in this element (may define a narrower value set?)." ] ;
